Regulatory Compliance and the USA PATRIOT Act Framework
The issuance and activation of the JaffPay/PlayCard are strictly governed by federal law, specifically the USA PATRIOT Act. This legislation, enacted to combat terrorism and money laundering, mandates that financial institutions verify the identity of every individual who opens an account.
The Identity Verification (KYC) Process
When a user attempts to activate the card at PlayCard.com/activate or via the 1-800-269-0185 number, they must undergo a Know Your Customer (KYC) screening. This process requires the collection of the individual’s full name, physical address (P.O. boxes are generally insufficient for full activation), date of birth, and Social Security Number or other government-issued ID number.
If an individual’s identity can only be partially verified, the card remains in a restricted state. In this "partial verification" mode, the card can typically be used for domestic in-store purchases, but advanced features are disabled.
